I was staying at the Pennsylvanian in Pittsburgh for a business trip, so it pleased me that there was a place for me to get a haircut in the same building.  Jeanie did a great job on my hair.  She offered me a robe, so that my hair would not devour my clothes.  My stylist took time to cut my hair the way I wanted it and I could not be happier with the end result.  The view from my chair outlooking the window was a sight to behold.  The cleanliness of a salon is high on my list of priorities and Sognatore passed that test.  The price for a men's haircut is $26, so it is rather steep for some.  Sognatore is closed Sunday & Monday.  I would also recommend making a reservation.

