gr6AoBJ5MEkZynXP_MHs1w
The Omni William Penn Hotel definitely has the best hotel employees I have ever encountered.  Everywhere I went, from the maids, lobby clerks, to the bellhops...they all asked me how my stay was.  They were all eager to help and ready to answer any question I had.  Pittsburgh is an old town and thus, the hotel reflected that.  It isn't old such that there are cobwebs and ghosts in the attic but rather colonial old money.  You get a feeling that you are of the Bourgeoisie class staying here.  Men & women in suits and dresses  litter the lobby area.  I cannot comment on the pricing because I was here on my company dime.  I also did not try the food/room service.  Bath & room items were always replenished on need.  Linens were changed.  Free HBO on TVs.  The hotel foyer & lobby area has a starbucks for coffee addicts and an obligatory overpriced gift shop for those wanting to purchase a Steelers Terrible Towel for $11.99.

