I know what I want my grave to be made out of.  Pamela's Strawberry Hotcakes.  It is to die for.  "Crepe hotcakes stuffed with fresh strawberries, brown sugar, sour cream and topped with whipped cream."  The first bite of that brown sugar + crispy crepe sent sensations into my mouth unbeknown from breakfast foods.  I have had plenty of early morning grub but most of my experiences were average.  It is not hard to scramble a few eggs, fry some bacon, and mash some hashbrowns.     Pamela's Diner is now at the top of my list for breakfast.  Along with the Obama-approved hot cake, I had eggs, sausage and toast.  My friend's waffle, omelet, and potatoes were good as well.  This Pamela's location is cash only and parking can be hard to find in this district.  The atmosphere is lively and fun.  The waitress to customer ratio is high.  The wait can be long during peak hours.

